    "body" : "<p>With IntelliJ IDEA 2021.2.1 (Ultimate Edition) at least, you can simply do:</p>\n<p>Select-All,\nEdit &gt; Join Lines</p>\n<p>(Windows: ctrl-A, ctrl-shift-J with default mapping.)\nThis places everyting on one line, so no indentation or linebreaks.  However, there will be a space after commas and before/after colons, if your code style is set for that.</p>\n"
